## Loading R packages

In the code chunk below, [`p_load()`](https://www.rdocumentation.org/packages/pacman/versions/0.5.1/topics/p_load) of [pacman](https://github.com/trinker/pacman) package is used to load tidyverse family of packages.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(tidyverse)
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
realis <- read_csv("data/realis2019.csv")
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = realis,
       aes(x = `Unit Price ($ psm)`)) +
  geom_histogram()
```
